title: Mental Outfitters (Logo) - Performance Enhancing Knowledge and Skills!
description: We provide content, courses, and coaching focused on performance enhancing knowledge and skills for professionals.
other_notes:
We have chosen our name because and outfitter is "a business providing equipment, supplies, and often trained guides" So we envision our online site as a place that provides guides (coaching and courses) as well as equipment/supplies (templates - presentation, excel, word docs, emails, etc.)
Logo Feeling: We are not trying to be a snobby coaching site that acts like we are going to lead you to the promise land or help you ascend a mountain. We aren't going to have pictures of ourselves in business attire leaning against an office window in the big city. So basic logos or corporate feeling is not what we are going for. The competition in our space is all over the board. Most designs/logos are boring and way to corporate/business feeling. We are trying to be more interesting and approach it differently - more fun light-hearted and cooler!
We want bold and fun with color. Possible character or other visual representation. What we do want is to make the customer feel like they can get help, learn, and enjoy their journey in their career...and have fun in doing it.
Design wise we are open and don’t have a direction in mind at the moment. We do like to use various colors in our presentations so they are not drab.
Things to stay away from:
- Lightbulb concepts (It has been done a lot)
- Face/head outlines (One of the main competitors uses a face/head)
- Tree concepts (it has been done a lot)
- Mountains (it has been done a lot)
What we are looking for:
- Non Corporate/flat logos. Our space has a ton of corporate looking logos/sites.
- Depth and Feeling
- Fresh/Cool/Fun - Should make you feel like this site/these people might be fun to learn from.
- Color
Some ideas (people are asking for potential direction ideas. Here are our thoughts:
- A compass with brain in the middle
- A brain with pieces
- A brain with business components coming out of it (documents, charts, pencil, keyboard, etc)
- A character/animal that looks like it is taking an adventure trip (but for business)
- Mental Models (Look up on google "Mental Models" on google images) We use this a lot in our training to explain concepts. Maybe that can spark an idea.
We ask that you also try to think outside the box and see if you can't wow us with something we aren't thinking about.
Hope this helps! And thanks for all your hard work on this!

title: Create a joyful and hopeful logo design for New Mourning
description:
We provide counseling for those who have experienced a loss (which could be loss of life of family or friend or loss of relationship via divorce or something else) related to many things in life that could lead to depression and loss of hope for life going forward. We have been in the business of helping those who have lost hope to find hope and to take their loss and turn it into purpose so that they spend the remaining years using their loss for good.... turning lemons into lemonade. Mourning can be changed by turning it into a NEW morning. When you wake up and have a new start to the day. Mourning can be positive if you make it something turned toward others or in other words - without "U" in the word. Mourning without the U is Morning. A new start.
Our slogan is "Living Forward After Grief" - Someone loses a loved one or has tragedy in their life they typically get stuck in circular thinking being unable to get out of the depression, NewMourning Podcast has been created to discuss how to help people "live forward" use the loss to help others and themselves, understanding that the loss is real and will always be there but can be used an instrument of positive change in their lives.

We want the logo to show hope. Maybe a Rising Sun or something related (Open to your creative concepts).

title: New Buffalo Wing restaurant needs powerful logo
description:
At THAT Wing Spot wings aren’t just wings, they’re an experience. It’s why all the food we share with you is made fresh from scratch, from the sauces to the meat, without the use of any steroids or hormones. After all, we feel the food we make should be as natural as the passion we put into it and should bring you as much satisfaction as we get from making it. We want our wings to be your favorite. Our commitment to being your favorite wing spot to dine reaches further than excellent cuisine. We want to create a full flavor experience for you with each bite. We want to be a part of each. We believe a meal is more than satisfying your stomach, it should speak to your soul and have you eager for more. Our mission won’t be completed until we’ve completely won you over and become your go-to favorite spot for wings. Because, at the end of the day, we’re not here to just be THAT Wing Spot, we’re here to be YOUR Wing Spot.
We are very open to many ideas and suggestions. We would like to see design ideas that you think would be the best fit to depict our concept. We have also been toying around with the idea of a chicken wing character or chicken wing symbol of some sort being incorporated into the logo (because it is our central food item), so we would love to see some designs with that incorporated as well – however, that is NOT at all necessary, the right word art logo can work perfectly, too. As for colors, we are VERY open to all creative ideas and suggestions. If there is one color that you think would best represent our brand, we’d love to see it and know your thoughts behind it.
Our concept for this restaurant is to be solely providing the absolute best buffalo-style fried chicken wings, completely winning in the areas of flavor, texture, taste, quality, consistency, service, and hospitality. We only use fresh premium chicken wings that are all-natural, hormone, steroid, and antibiotic-free. All of our chicken wings are made to order and are immediately served so our customers/guests may enjoy them at their peak quality. We make all of our wing sauces and dipping sauces in house completely from scratch.
We desire to be our guests’ “Go-to”wing spot for all occasions (lunch, dinner, parties, sporting events, etc.). We strive to be our guests FAVORITE spot for wings.
Our main menu offerings are simple – buffalo-style fried chicken wings available to be tossed in a variety of scratch made sauces or dry rubs, dipping sauces (buttermilk ranch and bleu cheese) and crispy crinkle-cut french fries. All of our items are made from scratch to be full of flavor and with good quality ingredients. We are all about feel-good food that is made good for you. We use Chicken that is free of any hormones, steroids, or antibiotics. We hand bread all of our chicken. We mix and make all of our sauces in house. All of our food is made completely from scratch using fresh, quality ingredients. That being said, our menu items will be priced in the $10-$20 range.
We really want our logo to communicate who we are, what we do, the value we provide, and the freshness and authenticity of our food. We want this logo to be cool, modern, and desirable. We want this logo to pop and stand out and really communicate good strong vibes to each person who sees it. Ideally, they’d be drawn in to come learn more and feel confident in trying our wings after seeing the logo.
Please let us know if you have any questions, additional thoughts, or ideas!
Here is a list of somewhat similar Restaurant Concepts to draw inspiration from:
• Wing Spot
• Buffalo Wild Wings
• bb.q chikin
• Cosmic Wing
